Hey everyone, 

I'm trying to get a beamcore antimatter reactor to work. I though I had it working but when I'm in space, it says I am missing solid hydrogen, but I can't find a tank to place it in. Am I missing something?

If this is about KSP interstellar extended, may I suggest posting this in the KSP interstellar extended thread? KSPIE is a hefty mod with lots of complex features so you might find the answer you're looking for in one of the guides or in the mod thread itself if others have asked the same question before.
Ok I will try there, I read through and didn't find anything about an antimatter beam core reactor using solid hydrogen.
